{
  "texts": [
    "First, facilitators build maps with human participants by asking follow-up questions until an answer becomes tangential.",
    "For example, frequent household quarrels are a risk for suicide ideation in children, and a divorce can fuel such tensions.",
    "However, a facilitator would not venture into detailing the risk factors for divorce when building a map of youth suicide.",
    "Based on this observation, the system could locally adapt the number of iterations until hitting an out-of-topic concept, instead of being constrained by a global parameter.",
    "Second, many PLMs such as GPT rely on their billions of trained parameters to encode their knowledge of the world."
  ]
}